1
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,267
<i>We've been trying
to contact you,</i>

2
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,067
<i>but no one is answering
the phone!</i>

3
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:46,167
<i> Hazel went after Miss Felma.</i>

4
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,900
<i>You should have
called me or Jeffrey!</i>

5
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:50,567
<i> You went after Felma?</i>

6
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:52,900
<i>I told you that she has
my husband and daughter,</i>

7
00:00:53,033 --> 00:00:54,000
<i> didn't I?</i>

8
00:00:54,133 --> 00:00:57,000
<i>But thank you for giving me
Felma's address.</i>

9
00:00:57,133 --> 00:00:58,367
<i> You're a monster, Hazel!</i>

10
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> I'll get you for this!</i>

11
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:01,333
<i>Why are you talking
to Manuel's wife?</i>

12
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:03,700
<i>Please don't tell
anyone about this.</i>

13
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:04,833
<i> In fact, I will help you.</i>

14
00:01:04,967 --> 00:01:06,700
<i>I wonder if Felma's hiding
Manuel.</i>

15
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:08,967
<i>Are you thinking that
I'm hiding Manuel?</i>

16
00:01:09,133 --> 00:01:10,100
<i>You really don't know
where he is?</i>

17
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:11,467
<i>We're not thinking that
you're hiding him,</i>

18
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,500
<i>but Hazel won't be going after
you if you don't know anything.</i>

19
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:15,167
<i> I'm not hiding him!</i>

20
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:16,400
<i>Coleen, do you know
anything about this?</i>

21
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:18,600
<i> Mom doesn't know where Dad is.</i>

22
00:01:18,733 --> 00:01:22,967
<i>If you don't stop now,
you will lose a sister.</i>

23
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:26,733
<i> Jessica?</i>

24
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:27,600
<i> Didang!</i>

25
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:28,567
<i> Where are you?</i>

26
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:31,200
<i>I thought I saw
Manuel's daughter.</i>

27
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:32,433
<i> I saw Jessica.</i>

28
00:01:32,567 --> 00:01:33,467
<i> She came out of our house.</i>

29
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:36,833
<i> Why do you have all that food?</i>

30
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:37,767
<i> Where are you bringing that?</i>

31
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:38,800
<i> Who is that for?</i>

32
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:43,700
<i>Didang, is that Jessica
I saw earlier?</i>

33
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:50,333
Didang!

34
00:01:50,467 --> 00:01:53,167
Are Manuel and Jessica here?

35
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,600
Did Coleen bring them here?

36
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:03,000
Didang, tell me the truth!

37
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:04,433
<i> What?</i>

38
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:05,833
<i> Are they here?</i>

39
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,300
<i> Are you hiding them here?</i>

40
00:02:12,133 --> 00:02:13,333
Didang, tell me the truth!

41
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,167
Are Manuel and Jessica
hiding here?

42
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:17,133
Mom! What's going on?

43
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:20,000
Are you hiding Manuel
and Jessica here?

44
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:27,767
<i>Coleen, why did you come
in from the back door?</i>

45
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:29,233
<i>I just checked something
from the laundry.</i>

46
00:02:29,367 --> 00:02:32,233
<i> My ID is in my uniform.</i>

47
00:02:32,367 --> 00:02:33,900
<i> Why do you have so much food?</i>

48
00:02:34,033 --> 00:02:34,967
<i> Who is that for?</i>

49
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:36,933
<i> It's for me, Miss Felma.</i>

50
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:39,833
<i>I want to have a meal
in the laundry area.</i>

51
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:41,400
<i>I want to eat while
doing the laundry.</i>

52
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:42,967
- Oh, really?
- Wait, Miss Felma!

53
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,200
- Where are you going?
- What? What?

54
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:46,033
Aren't we supposed to go out?

55
00:02:46,167 --> 00:02:47,400
We're going to get groceries.

56
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:48,467
We're going to the market.

57
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,700
And we're getting a massage.

58
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:51,067
I also want to watch a movie.

59
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,300
Don't go anywhere.

60
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:54,700
<i> Oh, and it's dirty back there.</i>

61
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:55,700
<i> It's gross.</i>

62
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:57,633
<i>I haven't cleaned up
back there yet.</i>

63
00:02:57,767 --> 00:03:00,300
Didang, I'm used to
that kind of stuff.

64
00:03:00,433 --> 00:03:03,867
Mom, there are rodents
and cockroaches there.

65
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,867
Why?

66
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,600
Did you go there?

67
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:08,733
Did you go inside?

68
00:03:08,867 --> 00:03:09,800
Jessica.

69
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:15,233
Please, don't try to stop me!

70
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:16,867
I know I'm right!

71
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,167
Manuel is here! Right?

72
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:19,133
You two!

73
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:19,933
Mom! Mom!

74
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:20,900
- Manuel!
- Miss Felma!

75
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:22,000
- Miss Felma!
- Manuel are you there?

76
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:23,467
There are flying
cockroaches in there! Don't!

77
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,100
<i> Let me clean it up first.</i>

78
00:03:27,233 --> 00:03:27,967
<i> Don't go inside.</i>

79
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,267
<i> Let me clean it up.</i>

80
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,300
<i>- Mom!
- Manuel!</i>

81
00:03:32,433 --> 00:03:33,133
<i>- Mom!
- Manuel!</i>

82
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:34,833
- Manuel!
- Let me clean up first.

83
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:35,533
Miss...

84
00:03:39,233 --> 00:03:40,300
Manuel!

85
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,767
So you're here!

86
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:59,067
Roger, thank you.

87
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,600
Good morning, Sir.

88
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:05,333
Sir, Miss Claire told me that
my mom didn't come back here?

89
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:06,633
That's right.

90
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:07,633
Thank you.

91
00:04:09,133 --> 00:04:10,867
Ma'am Jessica?

92
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,867
Yes.

93
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:12,900
There is no problem that
can't be resolved

94
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:15,133
through a sincere conversation.

95
00:04:15,267 --> 00:04:17,033
I hope everything goes well
for you.

96
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:50,533
Hello?

97
00:04:50,667 --> 00:04:52,467
Hello, Ma'am Hazel.

98
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,100
I have good news.

99
00:04:54,233 --> 00:04:56,000
Ma'am, Jessica's back.

100
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:58,233
She's on her way up.

101
00:04:58,367 --> 00:04:59,200
Really?

102
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,967
Thank you, Sir.

103
00:05:01,133 --> 00:05:03,667
I'll finally see my daughter.

104
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,100
I hope you patch things up
with her.

105
00:05:06,233 --> 00:05:07,400
Thank you.

106
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:31,000
- Dad!
- Coleen!

107
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:32,967
- Why is your father here?
- Dad!

108
00:05:35,533 --> 00:05:36,700
When did this happen?

109
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:37,900
How did he end up here?

110
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:41,067
-Felma, don't get mad at Coleen.
-I'm not talking to you!

111
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,367
I'm talking to my daughter

112
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,200
Why did you bring them here?

113
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:48,133
Mom, Miss Hazel found them
at their place.

114
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:50,700
I don't know where else
I can bring them.

115
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:53,767
Of all places, you really
have to bring them here?

116
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,833
You lied to me!

117
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:58,033
You too, Didang!

118
00:05:58,167 --> 00:06:00,700
I can't believe you
conspired with them!

119
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:04,833
Miss Felma, I just feel bad
for them.

120
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:07,067
And you don't feel bad for me?

121
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,400
Why did you do this to me?

122
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:12,567
You made a fool out of me!

123
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:16,400
I stood up to your siblings.

124
00:06:16,533 --> 00:06:18,267
To Paz and Noah!

125
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:21,000
And especially Hazel!

126
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:23,800
Only to find out that
they were right all along!

127
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:31,533
I'm hiding your father
without me knowing!

128
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:32,900
You made a fool out of me!

129
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,133
Felma.

130
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:36,967
Felma, wait.

131
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,333
Please, don't get mad at her.

132
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:39,433
It's not her fault.

133
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:41,867
Shut up, Manuel!

134
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:44,000
I'm sorry, Mom.

135
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:48,533
I don't know how to tell you
because you will get mad at me.

136
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,733
We're supposed to be
on the same page

137
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:53,667
when it comes to your dad!

138
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:59,433
Only to be betrayed by you!

139
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:00,500
Felma, we're leaving.

140
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:01,967
I'm just waiting for Jessica.

141
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:03,633
Don't wait for her here!

142
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:07,000
Wait for her somewhere else!

143
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,200
Mom, please don't do this.

144
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:12,533
Have pity on him!

145
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:14,700
Have pity on him?

146
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,067
You betrayed me!

147
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:21,367
Didang, get him out of here.

148
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,367
Didang!

149
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,433
Yes, Ma'am.

150
00:07:26,567 --> 00:07:28,567
Didang.

151
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,367
You don't have to do anything,
I'll do it myself.

152
00:07:32,133 --> 00:07:34,700
If my mom doesn't want to help,
I'm not going to force her.

153
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:37,600
I want to be with my dad.

154
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:40,333
So I'm coming with him.

155
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:42,167
Coleen!

156
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:02,333
Yes, I'm the one who talked
to you about the apartment.

157
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,633
I'm going to pay
the two months' advance

158
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:07,667
and one month's deposit.

159
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:10,433
Yes, thank you.

160
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,200
Stop it, Coleen!

161
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:32,400
I'm serious, Mom.

162
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:35,900
I don't want to miss the
chance to be with my dad.

163
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:39,433
No, sweetie, you have to stay
with your mom.

164
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:40,700
Okay?

165
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,667
You know that Jessica and I
won't be staying here long,

166
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,400
remember?

167
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:46,900
And we can't be together.

168
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:49,133
But, Dad...

169
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,433
Dad, I want to spend
more time with you.

170
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:54,333
I want to be with you.

171
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,600
Ever since I was a child,

172
00:08:56,733 --> 00:08:59,733
I've dreamed every day
of what it would be like

173
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:01,600
to have a father.

174
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:08,733
That's why, those moments
when we're together,

175
00:09:08,867 --> 00:09:10,433
even if they're stolen moments,
Dad...

176
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:12,333
Even if it's just
for a short while,

177
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:15,300
I'm already so happy.

178
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:18,933
But it's not enough, Dad.

179
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:22,600
I want to spend
more time with you.

180
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:33,400
I'm sorry, Mom.

181
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:35,100
But I'm coming with him.

182
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:37,500
It doesn't matter where he goes.

183
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,700
Coleen.

184
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,667
Coleen, you can't go with him.

185
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:47,700
You can't go with your father.

186
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,233
Didang, get him out of here.

187
00:09:49,367 --> 00:09:50,300
Dad!

188
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:52,333
- Get him out.
- Dad.

189
00:09:52,467 --> 00:09:53,433
Dad!

190
00:09:53,567 --> 00:09:55,967
You can't go with him!

191
00:09:56,100 --> 00:10:01,633
- Dad! Dad! Dad!
- That's enough!

192
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,667
Dad!

193
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:08,300
Dad!

194
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:12,133
- That's enough, stop it.
- I want to go with him!

195
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:15,767
It's okay, stay with your mom.

196
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:17,333
Come on.

197
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:18,400
We have to go.

198
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:20,033
- Go on.
- Dad!

199
00:10:20,167 --> 00:10:21,267
- Dad!
- Go on, Didang.

200
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,733
Dad!

201
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:36,133
Hello, my sweet little traitor.

202
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:37,467
Mommy!

203
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,467
Don't you miss me, sweetie?

204
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:59,100
Mommy, mommy, stop!

205
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:02,133
Mommy!

206
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:03,867
Mommy, stop!

207
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,900
Let me go!

208
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:11,467
Mommy!

209
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,400
Mommy!

210
00:11:14,467 --> 00:11:15,967
Mommy, why are you here?

211
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:18,533
I have my ways!

212
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:20,567
When I want something, I get it.

213
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:22,133
- Always!
- No!

214
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:23,067
Did you really think

215
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,200
you and your dad could get away
from me?

216
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:28,200
Now, tell me, where is your dad?

217
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,733
Where is he?

218
00:11:31,867 --> 00:11:33,333
- Come here!
- Mom!

219
00:11:33,467 --> 00:11:34,500
We have to talk!

220
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:36,400
Mom!

221
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:38,700
Come here, Coleen!

222
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,200
Mom!

223
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:42,433
Would you really choose

224
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,300
someone you've only known
for a few days over us?

225
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:46,767
Than the ones who've been
with you your whole life?

226
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,767
He's not just anyone!

227
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,600
He's my father!

228
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:52,667
And do I really have to choose?

229
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,500
Yes!

230
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:58,433
Because you don't know how deep
the wound your father left

231
00:11:58,567 --> 00:12:00,333
in your older siblings is.

232
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:06,200
And if you go with them,
you'll only reopen that wound!

233
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:10,500
Mom, can't I be his daughter,
too?

234
00:12:10,633 --> 00:12:13,167
Andrea and Jeffrey
are my siblings.

235
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:16,333
And I'm his daughter.

236
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:21,567
Mom, please give me this chance.

237
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:25,933
If you don't want me
to go with them,

238
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:28,867
then let them stay here.

239
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,800
Why can't you just
let it go, Coleen?

240
00:12:33,267 --> 00:12:37,233
Aren't we enough?

241
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:40,967
Isn't our love enough?

242
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:42,400
No, Mom.

243
00:12:42,533 --> 00:12:43,300
That's not true.

244
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:45,500
When it comes to love,

245
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:49,833
you've given me
more than enough.

246
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,833
But...

247
00:12:51,967 --> 00:12:54,667
But when I met Dad...

248
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:57,800
I feel like I've discovered
who I am.

249
00:12:57,933 --> 00:13:03,400
I can't explain it,
but the way he smiled,

250
00:13:03,533 --> 00:13:04,700
the way he held me.

251
00:13:06,667 --> 00:13:09,533
The way he hugged me.

252
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:15,467
It's as if he filled the
void in my heart

253
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,967
that I didn't know I had.

254
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,967
Mom, the void in my heart...

255
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:28,167
Perhaps Dad has something to do
with it.

256
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,833
When he left us.

257
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:36,433
But I think only Dad can fix it.

258
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:51,433
Don't cry.

259
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:54,733
Stop crying.

260
00:13:57,300 --> 00:14:02,500
I'm giving you permission
to let them stay here.

261
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:05,833
They can stay
as long as they need.

262
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:09,367
Really, Mom?

263
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,900
Are you sure?

264
00:14:11,033 --> 00:14:12,367
Thank you, Mom!

265
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:20,967
Mom, sorry.

266
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,333
Sorry for being difficult.

267
00:14:24,467 --> 00:14:26,400
I've been so stubborn.

268
00:14:36,433 --> 00:14:42,733
But, Mom, thank you
for letting me do this.

269
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:55,833
Why did they have to
run away from Hazel?

270
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:59,500
Why don't they just settle
things as a family?

271
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:01,867
Why drag other people into it?

272
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:10,333
Mom, Hazel is hurting them.

273
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:18,733
Maybe we could discuss this
with Andrea and Jeffrey.

274
00:15:18,867 --> 00:15:20,700
We can explain.

275
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,667
They might understand
their situation.

276
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:25,033
No.

277
00:15:25,167 --> 00:15:28,533
No, we can't.

278
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:32,133
They can't forgive your father.

279
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,567
He has another family now.

280
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,400
We're not a part of his life
anymore.

281
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:50,433
So, should we keep
this from them?

282
00:15:50,567 --> 00:15:53,800
They don't go out
that way anyway.

283
00:15:58,033 --> 00:16:01,100
You really are just
a kid, sweetie.

284
00:16:01,233 --> 00:16:04,967
You don't understand how deep
this situation really is.

285
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:11,167
You think it's all that simple.

286
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:16,400
Anyway, where's Didang?

287
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:18,700
I need to talk to her.

288
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:21,000
Manuel and Jessica can stay
in her room for now.

289
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:23,333
So they can be comfortable.

290
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:45,067
Sir Manuel?

291
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:45,933
Didang.

292
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:48,800
Didang, what happened?

293
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:52,067
What did Felma do to Coleen?

294
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:54,433
Did she reprimand her?

295
00:16:54,567 --> 00:16:58,000
Everything's fine, Sir.

296
00:16:58,133 --> 00:17:01,767
Miss Felma gave in.

297
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:05,467
She's letting you
stay here for now.

298
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,533
I caused trouble for them again.

299
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:13,833
We shouldn't have stayed here.

300
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:15,633
Don't worry about it.

301
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,367
I should apologize.

302
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,200
I didn't stop Miss Felma
from coming here.

303
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,967
You got caught because of me.

304
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,667
No, it's all my fault.

305
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,767
I dragged my daughter into this.

306
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,533
I even got you involved.

307
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:32,600
I end up hurting Felma again.

308
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:35,000
Don't worry too much.

309
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:38,433
Honestly, Miss Felma
understands your situation.

310
00:17:38,567 --> 00:17:41,733
Miss Felma is a kind person,
you know that.

311
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:46,167
I know, but even kindness
has its limits,

312
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,233
especially when people start
taking advantage of it.

313
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,867
Like what I'm doing now.

314
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:58,833
I know she only gave in
because of Coleen.

315
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:03,367
I don't want to
abuse her kindness.

316
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:06,067
Jessica and I really
should leave now.

317
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:09,100
What if Jeff and Andrea
find out later?

318
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:11,900
We should be more careful now,

319
00:18:12,033 --> 00:18:14,633
so they won't see us
and get caught.

320
00:18:14,767 --> 00:18:16,433
Right?

321
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:17,467
Don't worry, okay?

322
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:20,100
Here, I brought you
some food to eat.

323
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:21,900
You should eat it
while it's hot.

324
00:18:25,233 --> 00:18:28,467
Maximo, the deal is off.

325
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,667
I'm with my rebellious
daughter now.

326
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,367
Don't worry. You can keep the
down payment.

327
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:35,233
Bye.

328
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:39,300
Mommy!

329
00:18:39,433 --> 00:18:41,967
Mom!

330
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:44,867
Let me remind you,
we're in the Philippines.

331
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,467
There's no child services
for you to call!

332
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,700
So I'm telling you now,

333
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,133
if you don't want me
to hurt you,

334
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:52,533
you'd better tell me
where your dad is!

335
00:18:52,667 --> 00:18:53,933
Where is he? Tell me!

336
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:55,267
No, Mommy.

337
00:18:55,433 --> 00:18:59,033
Hurt me all you want,
but I won't tell you!

338
00:18:59,167 --> 00:18:59,933
Really?

339
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:08,800
You're not going to tell me?

340
00:19:08,933 --> 00:19:10,233
Tell me where he is!

341
00:19:10,367 --> 00:19:11,233
You're not going to tell me?

342
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:15,767
Tell me where he is!

343
00:19:19,767 --> 00:19:21,133
You're not going to tell me?

344
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:30,433
Miss Felma, you want to see me?

345
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:35,233
Didang...

346
00:19:35,367 --> 00:19:40,667
Can you let Manuel and Jessica
stay in your room for now?

347
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,900
Of course.

348
00:19:43,033 --> 00:19:49,333
I'm sorry for conspiring
with Coleen.

349
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,933
Am I doing the right thing,
Didang?

350
00:19:58,467 --> 00:20:00,033
Yes, you're doing the
right thing, Ma'am.

351
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:04,300
Forgiving me is the best
decision you can make.

352
00:20:04,467 --> 00:20:06,900
Right? I won't do it again.

353
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:09,700
I'm sorry.

354
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:12,467
That's not what I meant.

355
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,767
I don't know...

356
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:21,600
I'm talking about letting
Manuel and Jessica stay here.

357
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:23,533
Oh that.

358
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:24,567
Of course it is...

359
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:27,367
and even if it's the
wrong decision or not

360
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:32,267
at least you showed them
how kind you are.

361
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:36,033
You didn't withhold help
from Sir Manuel.

362
00:20:38,667 --> 00:20:42,767
Miss Felma, will you still
let Coleen see them

363
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:45,567
once they leave?

364
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,700
I don't know.

365
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,700
I honestly don't know.

366
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:57,667
But if it's just up to me,
I will let her see them.

367
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:01,867
But you're worrying
about Jeff and Andrea?

368
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,967
Yes, it's so hard.

369
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:10,600
Andrea meant it when she
threatened Coleen

370
00:21:10,767 --> 00:21:12,500
that she would lose a sister.

371
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:16,467
But I don't want to deny Coleen
her chance

372
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:18,667
to be with her father.

373
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:24,033
Oh my, you're in
a tough situation.

374
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:25,533
It is so tough.

375
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:30,433
That's why Manuel can't
stay here for too long.

376
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:36,200
If Jeff and Andrea find out
about this,

377
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:38,367
they might turn away from me,
too.

378
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:46,833
Dad, you know what,

379
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:48,967
Miss Didang's room is better
than this place,

380
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,567
and you're safer there.

381
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:51,567
And the bathroom is closer.

382
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,767
Sure, but I feel bad for Didang.

383
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:55,367
We're fine here.

384
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:56,467
Come on, Dad.

385
00:21:56,600 --> 00:21:59,233
I'm sure Miss Didang
doesn't mind.

386
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:01,400
Right, but I'll be out of here
anyway.

387
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:03,133
I'm just waiting for Jessica
to come back.

388
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:06,967
Dad, there's no need to rush.

389
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:12,167
Speaking of Jessica,
I need to call her.

390
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:14,500
She might be in
the apartment now.

391
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:16,333
Wait, I'll call her.

392
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,567
That's enough.

393
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:37,000
Put ice on your face to keep it
from swelling.

394
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:41,633
Here.

395
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:50,400
You did this to yourself.

396
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:55,200
You should have just told me
where your dad is.

397
00:22:55,333 --> 00:23:00,367
You wouldn't have been hurt,
and we won't have any problem.

398
00:23:04,233 --> 00:23:06,467
I won't tell you, Mommy.

399
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,500
Oh no!

400
00:23:17,633 --> 00:23:18,767
I didn't have my phone.

401
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,067
I left it in my room, charging.

402
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,133
I'm just going to get it.

403
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:23,067
Okay.

404
00:23:25,433 --> 00:23:26,867
Didang.

405
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,167
Sir Manuel.

406
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:29,667
I'll just fix up my room

407
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:32,067
so everything's ready for you
to move in later.

408
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,933
Wait, can I borrow your phone?

409
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:37,333
Okay, here.

410
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:38,400
Thank you.

411
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:41,967
Put it on speaker phone,
sweetie.

412
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:43,300
Okay.

413
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:50,000
You know, Jessica,
when I was a kid,

414
00:23:50,133 --> 00:23:53,633
my mom had a way to make me
tell the truth.

415
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,433
You want me to show you how?

416
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:05,600
No, Mommy.

417
00:24:08,467 --> 00:24:09,333
No.

418
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,433
No!

419
00:24:15,567 --> 00:24:16,400
No! Mommy!

420
00:24:16,533 --> 00:24:19,167
Give it back!

421
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:20,433
Miss D?

422
00:24:20,567 --> 00:24:21,333
Who is this?

423
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:27,067
Who is this?

424
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:29,267
Is she the one who
helped you last time?

425
00:24:29,433 --> 00:24:30,367
Is she the person Felma sent

426
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:31,467
- to help you escape?
- Mommy, give it back!

427
00:24:35,667 --> 00:24:36,933
Hello, Jessica. Where are you?

428
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:39,700
She's with me.

429
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:44,800
Hazel?

430
00:24:44,933 --> 00:24:46,133
<i> Hello, Manuel.</i>

431
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:47,467
Give it back.

432
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,367
Surprise.

433
00:24:49,500 --> 00:24:51,500
I think it's time
for a family reunion.

434
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:53,900
What do you think?

435
00:24:54,033 --> 00:24:56,067
If you want to see Jessica,

436
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,533
you have to come here right now.

437
00:24:57,667 --> 00:25:00,133
No, Dad! Don't listen to her!

438
00:25:00,267 --> 00:25:02,533
<i> Stay out of this!</i>

439
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:03,533
That's bad manners!

440
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:07,300
- Dad.
- Hello?

441
00:25:07,433 --> 00:25:08,800
So what now?

442
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:10,500
Are you coming here?

443
00:25:10,633 --> 00:25:11,900
Or you want us to come to you?

444
00:25:12,033 --> 00:25:13,100
We'll come pick you up.

445
00:25:13,233 --> 00:25:14,433
No! No!

446
00:25:14,567 --> 00:25:15,700
<i> No! Mom!</i>

447
00:25:17,467 --> 00:25:19,933
Hazel, please just leave us be.

448
00:25:20,067 --> 00:25:21,433
Come on, let Jessica go.

449
00:25:21,567 --> 00:25:23,500
Didn't you say
I'm just a burden?

450
00:25:23,633 --> 00:25:26,567
Why are you chasing us?

451
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,000
<i> Idiot!</i>

452
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:30,267
Because you're my husband.

453
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:33,033
<i>You're mine,
do you understand that?</i>

454
00:25:33,167 --> 00:25:34,467
<i> And even if you're a burden...</i>

455
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,567
you're still my husband!

456
00:25:37,567 --> 00:25:38,767
And believe it or not...

457
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,433
I still love you.

458
00:25:42,567 --> 00:25:45,067
Hazel, whatever you're doing
is not love.

459
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:47,467
You just don't want
to let me go.

460
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:50,467
Hazel, please, I'm begging you.

461
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,700
I just want a peaceful life.

462
00:25:52,833 --> 00:25:55,100
Let Jessica go.

463
00:25:55,233 --> 00:25:58,567
If you still want to see
your daughter, come over here.

464
00:25:58,700 --> 00:25:59,333
Right now!

465
00:25:59,467 --> 00:26:00,433
No, Dad!

466
00:26:00,567 --> 00:26:03,300
No matter what happens,
don't come here, Dad!

467
00:26:03,433 --> 00:26:04,633
Hazel!

468
00:26:07,467 --> 00:26:08,967
No, Mom!

469
00:26:09,133 --> 00:26:10,267
Mom!

470
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,833
Mom, no!

471
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:12,700
No!

472
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:17,867
Help! Help me!

473
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:18,767
Mom!

474
00:26:22,367 --> 00:26:24,200
Help me!

475
00:26:26,967 --> 00:26:29,467
I agreed to let your dad
stay here longer.

476
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:31,600
It's not part of our deal
to get involved

477
00:26:31,733 --> 00:26:33,100
in their family feud.

478
00:26:33,233 --> 00:26:35,200
Can you come pick me up here
instead?

479
00:26:35,333 --> 00:26:37,067
You're making me walk.

480
00:26:40,067 --> 00:26:41,900
Miss, I'm sorry.

481
00:26:43,967 --> 00:26:44,900
What took you so long?

482
00:26:45,033 --> 00:26:45,933
I've been waiting for you
for quite a while now.

483
00:26:46,067 --> 00:26:47,400
Let's go. Come on.

484
00:26:47,533 --> 00:26:48,500
Miss!

485
00:26:48,633 --> 00:26:50,100
Miss you left this!

486
00:26:50,233 --> 00:26:51,433
How's Jessica?

487
00:26:51,567 --> 00:26:53,433
Mom, she still hasn't
answered her phone.

488
00:26:53,567 --> 00:26:54,400
What secret are you talking
about?

489
00:26:54,533 --> 00:26:56,400
Is it about Coleen's father
again?

490
00:26:56,533 --> 00:26:58,533
You don't care about him,
don't you?

491
00:26:58,667 --> 00:27:00,133
Can you just leave us be?

492
00:27:00,267 --> 00:27:01,133
Let's go, Mom.

493
00:27:01,267 --> 00:27:03,000
- You're so rude!
- Wait.

494
00:27:03,133 --> 00:27:04,767
- You're too much.
- That's enough, Andrea!

495
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:06,267
Coleen, that's enough!

496
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:09,033
- You better stop!
- And you're going to hurt me!

497
00:27:09,167 --> 00:27:10,967
Ouch! You're hurting me!

498
00:27:11,100 --> 00:27:12,267
- Stop it!
- You're taking it too far!
